sub_title: Student at RSM Erasmus University | Digital Marketing Freelancer
summary:
Since childhood, I have been driven by an endless curiosity about the world and have always had a strong interest in natural sciences. However, my true passion turned out to be social sciences. In high school, I explored topics such as economics, marketing, finance, management, and entrepreneurship through various courses, volunteering, and experimenting with small-scale side hustles.

Currently, I am an International Business Administration student at Erasmus University Rotterdam, a globally renowned institution that values being a force for positive change. As part of the program, I have studied the latest developments in business management.

Through my professional experiences, I have developed advanced expertise in marketing. After a high-paced and extremely valuable internship as a PPC marketer, I realized that I can help small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) reach their marketing goals as a freelancer, using my skills and ideas.

My long-term goal is to become a catalyst for the development of my home country, Bulgaria, and to help it become a major European center for innovation and economic growth.
